            <line>When an ankheg grabs a Medium size or smaller creature, it pulls the creature into its space.</line>
            <line>An ankheg can move at normal speed while grabbing a Medium size or smaller creature, sliding the grabbed creature with it. It does not need to make a check or attack roll to do this, and its movement does not provoke <![CDATA[<i>opportunity attacks</i>]]> from the grabbed creature.</line>
         </block>
